  # Metadata Forge — Functional Specification
  
  > **See also:** [Architecture](architecture.md)
  
  ## 1. Purpose
  
  Metadata Forge automates the production and maintenance of GraalVM
  **reachability metadata** for community Java/Kotlin/Scala libraries. It lives
  inside the [`oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata)
  repository (hereafter "the reachability repo") and composes LLM-based
  code-generation agents with the repo's own build, test, and reporting
  pipelines to produce metadata, tests, and PRs ready for human review.
  
  ## 2. Scope
  
  The project covers three primary task families:
  
  1. **New library support** (`library-new-request`) — generate a JUnit (or
     Kotlin/Scala) test suite, produce reachability metadata, and open a PR for
     a previously unsupported library.
  2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of
     already-supported libraries (via the `library-update-request` pipeline).
  3. **Java compilation fixes** (`fixes-javac-fail`) — repair test sources that
     no longer compile against a bumped library version.
  4. **Java runtime fixes** (`fixes-java-run-fail`) — repair JVM-mode test
     failures that surface when raising a tested library to a new version.
  5. **Native-image runtime fixes** (`fixes-native-image-run-fail`) — update
     reachability metadata so `nativeTest` passes against the new library
     version, using the native metadata exploration phase.
  6. **Bulk version updates** (`library-bulk-update`) — record newly tested
     upstream versions for already-supported libraries when no fix is required.
  7. **Coverage improvement** (`library-update-request`) — increase
     dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.
  8. **Docker image updates** (`docker`) — refresh the allowed Docker images
     used by tests, including vulnerability rescans and version bumps.
  
  Out of scope: anything that does not produce reachability metadata or its
  supporting tests for the reachability repo.
  
  ## 3. Glossary
  
  | Term | Definition |
  | --- | --- |
  | **Reachability metadata** | JSON describing reflection, JNI, resource, serialization, and proxy access for a library, consumed by GraalVM `native-image`. |
  | **Reachability repo** | Local checkout or worktree of `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`. The build and metadata-generation Gradle tasks run inside it. The parent checkout of `forge/` is used by default. |
  | **Metrics root** | Directory that stores per-run results validated against [schemas/](../schemas/). By default, this is the run worktree's `forge/` directory. |
  | **Coordinate** | Maven coordinate of the target library, formatted `group:artifact:version`. |
  | **Agent** | LLM-driven code editor (Aider, Codex, or Pi) registered through [ai_workflows/agents/](../ai_workflows/agents/). Each implements `send_prompt`, `run_test_command`, `clear_context`. |
  | **Workflow strategy** | A registered control loop in [ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/) (e.g. `basic_iterative`, `dynamic_access_iterative`). |
  | **Predefined strategy** | Named, fully parameterized combination of agent + workflow strategy + prompts + parameters in [strategies/predefined_strategies.json](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json). Selected via `--strategy-name`. |
  | **Post-generation intervention** | Recovery step a strategy invokes when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` still fails. Pluggable via the `PostGenerationIntervention` registry. Configured per predefined strategy (`post-generation-intervention.name`). Concrete implementations: `noop`, `codex_then_pi` (default), `native_trace_collect`. See [workflow-strategies.md §5](workflow-strategies.md#5-post-generation-interventions). |
  | **Dynamic access** | Reflection, JNI, resource access, serialization, or proxy use that GraalVM `native-image` cannot determine statically. |
  | **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |
  | **Source context** | Read-only files supplied to the agent. Types: `main` (library source), `test` (upstream tests), `documentation` (Javadoc). Selected by the strategy parameter `source-context-types`. |
  
  ## 4. Configuration Contracts
  
  ### 4.1 Top-level worker bootstrap
  
  - `do-work.sh` is a fixed bootstrap script and must not be changed for worker
    behavior updates. Its only user-facing input is the selected branch; it
    forwards `argv` unchanged to `do_up_to_date_work.sh`, where every option and
    environment concern is handled.
  - `do_up_to_date_work.sh` owns argument parsing, environment normalization,
    Forge self-updates, queue dispatch, sleep timing, and re-execing the latest
    worker script.
  
  ### 4.2 CLI inputs (common to all entry scripts)
  
  - `--coordinates <group:artifact:version>` — required.
  - `--reachability-metadata-path` — overrides default reachability-repo clone.
  - `--metrics-repo-path` — overrides default metrics-repo clone.
  - `--strategy-name <name>` — selects an entry from `predefined_strategies.json`.
  - `--docs-path` — additional read-only files for agent context.
  - `-v` / `--verbose` — verbose agent output.
  - `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access
    strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).
  
  ### 4.3 Predefined strategy schema
  
  Each entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` must provide:
  
  - `name` — unique identifier passed via `--strategy-name`.
  - `agent` — registered agent name (`aider`, `codex`, `pi`).
  - `workflow` — registered workflow strategy name.
  - `model` — agent-visible model identifier.
  - `prompts` — map of prompt-key → template path. Required keys depend on the
    workflow (e.g., `dynamic_access_iterative` requires
    `dynamic-access-iteration`).
  - `parameters` — workflow-specific parameters (iteration limits,
    `source-context-types`, etc.).
  - `mcps` — optional list of MCP server names.
  - `post-generation-intervention` — optional. Selects the recovery step
    invoked when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` fails. Shape:
    `{ "name": "<registered intervention>", "parameters": { … } }`. Omitted
    entries default to `codex_then_pi`. See
    [workflow-strategies.md §5](workflow-strategies.md#5-post-generation-interventions).
  
  ### 4.4 Environment
  
  - Either `GRAALVM_HOME` or `JAVA_HOME` must point to a GraalVM distribution.
    Both variables are then aligned to that distribution. If neither does, the
    workflow exits with an error.
  - `gh` CLI authenticated against the reachability repo is required for any
    script in `git_scripts/` or `complete_pipelines/`.
  - `FORGE_PARALLELISM` controls how many issue workflows the top-level worker
    may run concurrently. Valid values are `1` through `4`; the default is `1`.
  
  ## 5. Outputs
  
  - **Per-run metrics record** appended to
    `<metrics_repo>/{script_run_metrics,benchmark_run_metrics}/<workflow>.json`,
    schema-validated. Successful run metrics are written under
    `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`.
  - **Generated tests + metadata + index.json** committed on the feature branch
    `ai/add-lib-support-<group>-<artifact>-<version>` in the reachability repo.
  - **Pull request** (only when invoked through `complete_pipelines/` or
    `git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`).
  
  ## 6. Failure Semantics
  
  Every workflow returns one of three statuses:
  
  | Status | Meaning |
  | --- | --- |
  | `RUN_STATUS_SUCCESS` | All gates passed; metadata and tests committed. |
  | `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` | Tests succeeded after the configured `PostGenerationIntervention` modified the working tree (e.g. `codex_then_pi` removing failing tests via Pi). The intervention's record is included in the run-metrics and PR description. PR-eligible. |
  | `RUN_STATUS_FAILURE` | The workflow could not converge or a quality gate failed; the feature branch is reset to the scaffold checkpoint and no PR is opened. |
  
  The exit code is `0` for the first two and `1` for failure.
  
  ## 7. Workflow Specifications
  
  - [Workflow strategies](workflow-strategies.md) — registry of strategies
    and post-generation interventions, including the
    [`native_trace_collect`](workflow-strategies.md#53-native_trace_collect)
    intervention that drives the trace loop.
  - [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test
    generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.
  - [Native metadata exploration](native-metadata-exploration.md) —
    specification for the iterative trace loop (Gradle task contract,
    convergence rule, status enum, codex hand-off). Implements the
    `native_trace_collect` intervention.
  - [Java compilation / runtime failure fix workflow](fix-java-run-fail.md)
    — version-bump fix workflow shared by `fix_javac_fail` and
    `fix_java_run_fail`. Strategies in this family route through the
    configured post-generation intervention when `nativeTest` still fails.
  - [Coverage improvement workflow](improve-library-coverage.md) — generates
    additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library
    version, without modifying existing tests or bumping versions. Triggered by
    the `library-update-request` pipeline label.
  - (Future) Basic iterative workflow.
[recv] {"type": "message_start", "message": {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_UAYgVemM4Ugtfn4DtdLG3mDC|fc_0f7bc84cff7f28d60169f4fa552a5481a3a57dfe07d9e461dc", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Metadata Forge — Functional Specification\n\n> **See also:** [Architecture](architecture.md)\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nMetadata Forge automates the production and maintenance of GraalVM\n**reachability metadata** for community Java/Kotlin/Scala libraries. It lives\ninside the [`oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata)\nrepository (hereafter \"the reachability repo\") and composes LLM-based\ncode-generation agents with the repo's own build, test, and reporting\npipelines to produce metadata, tests, and PRs ready for human review.\n\n## 2. Scope\n\nThe project covers three primary task families:\n\n1. **New library support** (`library-new-request`) — generate a JUnit (or\n   Kotlin/Scala) test suite, produce reachability metadata, and open a PR for\n   a previously unsupported library.\n2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\n   already-supported libraries (via the `library-update-request` pipeline).\n3. **Java compilation fixes** (`fixes-javac-fail`) — repair test sources that\n   no longer compile against a bumped library version.\n4. **Java runtime fixes** (`fixes-java-run-fail`) — repair JVM-mode test\n   failures that surface when raising a tested library to a new version.\n5. **Native-image runtime fixes** (`fixes-native-image-run-fail`) — update\n   reachability metadata so `nativeTest` passes against the new library\n   version, using the native metadata exploration phase.\n6. **Bulk version updates** (`library-bulk-update`) — record newly tested\n   upstream versions for already-supported libraries when no fix is required.\n7. **Coverage improvement** (`library-update-request`) — increase\n   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\n8. **Docker image updates** (`docker`) — refresh the allowed Docker images\n   used by tests, including vulnerability rescans and version bumps.\n\nOut of scope: anything that does not produce reachability metadata or its\nsupporting tests for the reachability repo.\n\n## 3. Glossary\n\n| Term | Definition |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Reachability metadata** | JSON describing reflection, JNI, resource, serialization, and proxy access for a library, consumed by GraalVM `native-image`. |\n| **Reachability repo** | Local checkout or worktree of `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`. The build and metadata-generation Gradle tasks run inside it. The parent checkout of `forge/` is used by default. |\n| **Metrics root** | Directory that stores per-run results validated against [schemas/](../schemas/). By default, this is the run worktree's `forge/` directory. |\n| **Coordinate** | Maven coordinate of the target library, formatted `group:artifact:version`. |\n| **Agent** | LLM-driven code editor (Aider, Codex, or Pi) registered through [ai_workflows/agents/](../ai_workflows/agents/). Each implements `send_prompt`, `run_test_command`, `clear_context`. |\n| **Workflow strategy** | A registered control loop in [ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/) (e.g. `basic_iterative`, `dynamic_access_iterative`). |\n| **Predefined strategy** | Named, fully parameterized combination of agent + workflow strategy + prompts + parameters in [strategies/predefined_strategies.json](../strategies/predefined_strategies.json). Selected via `--strategy-name`. |\n| **Post-generation intervention** | Recovery step a strategy invokes when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` still fails. Pluggable via the `PostGenerationIntervention` registry. Configured per predefined strategy (`post-generation-intervention.name`). Concrete implementations: `noop`, `codex_then_pi` (default), `native_trace_collect`. See [workflow-strategies.md §5](workflow-strategies.md#5-post-generation-interventions). |\n| **Dynamic access** | Reflection, JNI, resource access, serialization, or proxy use that GraalVM `native-image` cannot determine statically. |\n| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n| **Source context** | Read-only files supplied to the agent. Types: `main` (library source), `test` (upstream tests), `documentation` (Javadoc). Selected by the strategy parameter `source-context-types`. |\n\n## 4. Configuration Contracts\n\n### 4.1 Top-level worker bootstrap\n\n- `do-work.sh` is a fixed bootstrap script and must not be changed for worker\n  behavior updates. Its only user-facing input is the selected branch; it\n  forwards `argv` unchanged to `do_up_to_date_work.sh`, where every option and\n  environment concern is handled.\n- `do_up_to_date_work.sh` owns argument parsing, environment normalization,\n  Forge self-updates, queue dispatch, sleep timing, and re-execing the latest\n  worker script.\n\n### 4.2 CLI inputs (common to all entry scripts)\n\n- `--coordinates <group:artifact:version>` — required.\n- `--reachability-metadata-path` — overrides default reachability-repo clone.\n- `--metrics-repo-path` — overrides default metrics-repo clone.\n- `--strategy-name <name>` — selects an entry from `predefined_strategies.json`.\n- `--docs-path` — additional read-only files for agent context.\n- `-v` / `--verbose` — verbose agent output.\n- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\n  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\n\n### 4.3 Predefined strategy schema\n\nEach entry in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` must provide:\n\n- `name` — unique identifier passed via `--strategy-name`.\n- `agent` — registered agent name (`aider`, `codex`, `pi`).\n- `workflow` — registered workflow strategy name.\n- `model` — agent-visible model identifier.\n- `prompts` — map of prompt-key → template path. Required keys depend on the\n  workflow (e.g., `dynamic_access_iterative` requires\n  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\n- `parameters` — workflow-specific parameters (iteration limits,\n  `source-context-types`, etc.).\n- `mcps` — optional list of MCP server names.\n- `post-generation-intervention` — optional. Selects the recovery step\n  invoked when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` fails. Shape:\n  `{ \"name\": \"<registered intervention>\", \"parameters\": { … } }`. Omitted\n  entries default to `codex_then_pi`. See\n  [workflow-strategies.md §5](workflow-strategies.md#5-post-generation-interventions).\n\n### 4.4 Environment\n\n- Either `GRAALVM_HOME` or `JAVA_HOME` must point to a GraalVM distribution.\n  Both variables are then aligned to that distribution. If neither does, the\n  workflow exits with an error.\n- `gh` CLI authenticated against the reachability repo is required for any\n  script in `git_scripts/` or `complete_pipelines/`.\n- `FORGE_PARALLELISM` controls how many issue workflows the top-level worker\n  may run concurrently. Valid values are `1` through `4`; the default is `1`.\n\n## 5. Outputs\n\n- **Per-run metrics record** appended to\n  `<metrics_repo>/{script_run_metrics,benchmark_run_metrics}/<workflow>.json`,\n  schema-validated. Successful run metrics are written under\n  `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`.\n- **Generated tests + metadata + index.json** committed on the feature branch\n  `ai/add-lib-support-<group>-<artifact>-<version>` in the reachability repo.\n- **Pull request** (only when invoked through `complete_pipelines/` or\n  `git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`).\n\n## 6. Failure Semantics\n\nEvery workflow returns one of three statuses:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| `RUN_STATUS_SUCCESS` | All gates passed; metadata and tests committed. |\n| `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` | Tests succeeded after the configured `PostGenerationIntervention` modified the working tree (e.g. `codex_then_pi` removing failing tests via Pi). The intervention's record is included in the run-metrics and PR description. PR-eligible. |\n| `RUN_STATUS_FAILURE` | The workflow could not converge or a quality gate failed; the feature branch is reset to the scaffold checkpoint and no PR is opened. |\n\nThe exit code is `0` for the first two and `1` for failure.\n\n## 7. Workflow Specifications\n\n- [Workflow strategies](workflow-strategies.md) — registry of strategies\n  and post-generation interventions, including the\n  [`native_trace_collect`](workflow-strategies.md#53-native_trace_collect)\n  intervention that drives the trace loop.\n- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\n  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\n- [Native metadata exploration](native-metadata-exploration.md) —\n  specification for the iterative trace loop (Gradle task contract,\n  convergence rule, status enum, codex hand-off). Implements the\n  `native_trace_collect` intervention.\n- [Java compilation / runtime failure fix workflow](fix-java-run-fail.md)\n  — version-bump fix workflow shared by `fix_javac_fail` and\n  `fix_java_run_fail`. Strategies in this family route through the\n  configured post-generation intervention when `nativeTest` still fails.\n- [Coverage improvement workflow](improve-library-coverage.md) — generates\n  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\n  version, without modifying existing tests or bumping versions. Triggered by\n  the `library-update-request` pipeline label.\n- (Future) Basic iterative workflow.\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777662549392}}
